## Summary

Adds config-level Policy conformance checks for ingress/channel access. This is observability only: it reports whether `openclaw` config conforms to the operator policy file, and does not add runtime enforcement.

```jsonc
{
  "ingress": {
    "session": { "requireDmScope": "per-channel-peer" },
    "channels": {
      "allowDmPolicies": ["pairing", "allowlist", "disabled"],
      "denyOpenGroups": true,
      "requireMentionInGroups": true
    }
  }
}
```

Scope support:

```jsonc
{
  "scopes": {
    "telegram-ingress": {
      "channelIds": ["telegram"],
      "ingress": {
        "channels": {
          "allowDmPolicies": ["pairing"],
          "denyOpenGroups": true,
          "requireMentionInGroups": true
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Notes for reviewers:

- `channelIds` scopes apply only to `ingress.channels.*`.
- `ingress.session.requireDmScope` remains top-level/global because the session scope is not channel-attributable.
- Evidence follows current runtime posture where known: omitted DM policy defaults to `pairing`; `dm.enabled=false` reports DM ingress as `disabled`; only supported `channels.defaults.groupPolicy` is inherited; configured `groups` imply allowlist posture; Slack-style `channels` entries do not imply allowlist posture; Telegram multi-account root groups are not inherited into named accounts; Feishu open groups default to no mention gate unless configured.
- Nested `groupPolicy` is not treated as runtime enforcement. Nested `requireMention` is still observed where runtime uses it.

## Verification

- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-85744-ingress-rebase node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=dot --testTimeout=30000` - 254 passed
- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`
- `node scripts/run-bundled-extension-oxlint.mjs`
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/policy-state.ts && git diff --check`
- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md`
- `~/.codex/skills/codex-review/scripts/codex-review --mode branch` - no accepted/actionable findings

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: config-level ingress conformance for DM scope, channel DM policy, open group posture, group mention gates, and `channelIds` scoped overlays.

Real environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 checkout under `/root/src/openclaw-policy-ingress-channel`.

Exact steps or command run after this patch: focused policy Vitest wrapper, extensions typecheck, bundled-extension oxlint, oxfmt/diff check, docs MDX check, and Codex review as listed above.

Evidence after fix: local proof passed after rebasing onto the updated sandbox policy branch; Codex review previously reported no discrete actionable correctness issues.

Observed result after fix: policy doctor/CLI tests pass with 253 tests, and ingress evidence now mirrors the reviewed runtime posture edge cases.

What was not tested: live channel message delivery was not exercised; this PR is config conformance only.

